# Bundle Size Optimization

## Defer Non-Critical Third-Party Libraries

Analytics, error tracking, and logging don't block user interaction. Load them after hydration:

```tsx
import dynamic from 'next/dynamic';

const Analytics = dynamic(
  () => import('@vercel/analytics/react').then((m) => m.Analytics),
  { ssr: false }
);

export const RootLayout = ({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) => {
  return (
    <html>
      <body>
        {children}
        <Analytics />
      </body>
    </html>
  );
};

export default RootLayout;
```

Candidates: Sentry `ErrorBoundary`, analytics scripts, chat widgets, cookie consent banners.

## Conditional Module Loading

Load heavy data or modules only when a feature is activated, not at import time:

```tsx
useEffect(() => {
  if (enabled && !data && typeof window !== 'undefined') {
    import('./heavy-animation-data.js')
      .then((mod) => setData(mod.frames))
      .catch(() => setEnabled(false));
  }
}, [enabled, data, setEnabled]);
```

The `typeof window !== 'undefined'` check prevents the module from being included in the SSR bundle.

## Preload on User Intent

Preload heavy bundles on hover/focus before the user clicks, eliminating perceived latency:

```tsx
const preload = () => {
  if (typeof window !== 'undefined') {
    void import('./monaco-editor');
  }
};

<button onMouseEnter={preload} onFocus={preload} onClick={openEditor}>
  Open Editor
</button>
```

## Use Ternary for Conditional Rendering

Prefer ternary over `&&` for conditional rendering to avoid accidentally rendering `0` or `""`:

```tsx
// Bad: renders "0" when count is 0
{count && <Badge count={count} />}

// Good: renders nothing when count is 0
{count > 0 ? <Badge count={count} /> : null}
```

## Hoist Static JSX Outside Components

JSX that never changes doesn't need to be recreated on every render:

```tsx
// Bad: re-created every render
export const Layout = ({ children }: Props) => {
  const footer = <footer>© 2026 Lumant</footer>;
  return (
    <div>
      {children}
      {footer}
    </div>
  );
};

// Good: created once at module level
const footer = <footer>© 2026 Lumant</footer>;

export const Layout = ({ children }: Props) => {
  return (
    <div>
      {children}
      {footer}
    </div>
  );
};
```

Source: Vercel React Best Practices
